PIN.values: |While it's always possible to use any (surface) mesh vertiex as point handle, you can also define specific point handle locations by adding them to your model beforehand. These can even be on the inside, like in this example.|
|Note in 3D tetrahedron indices are used for BoundedBiharmonicWeights- unlike triangle indices in 2D|
|Handles = No. of point handles + number of bone edges; cage edges not taken into account, as they are special point handles and count as such.&cr;&lf;|
|Please note: everything above this line can be precomputed, saved to disk/ioboxes and loaded from there|
|We still need to generate volumetric information for our surface mesh|
